# Epic 2: Visualizing and Analysing the Data

## Story 1: Import Required Libraries

The required Python libraries such as NumPy, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn, Scikit-learn, and XGBoost are imported to support data analysis, visualization, and machine learning model development.

## Story 2: Dataset Exploration

The dataset is loaded using the Pandas library. The structure of the dataset, feature names, target variable, data types, and dimensions are examined.

## Story 3: Univariate Analysis

Individual features are analyzed using histograms, box plots, and count plots to understand their distribution and identify anomalies.

## Story 4: Multivariate Analysis

Relationships between multiple variables are explored using correlation matrices, heatmaps, pair plots, and scatter plots.

## Story 5: Statistical Analysis

Descriptive statistics such as mean, median, standard deviation, minimum, and maximum values are calculated to summarize the dataset.